NON-DISCLOSURE AGREEMENT
Department of Justice
Criminal Investigations Division

---

This Non-Disclosure Agreement ("Agreement")
is entered into as of March 3, 2025,

between the Department of Justice,
Criminal Investigations Division
("the Division")

and the undersigned ("Employee").

---

1. CONFIDENTIAL INFORMATION

The Employee acknowledges that in the course
of their duties as Forensic Intelligence Analyst,

they will have access to information of a
sensitive and classified nature, including:

- active case files
- witness identities
- investigative methodologies
- internal communications
- evidentiary materials

The Employee agrees not to disclose,
reproduce, or distribute any such information

to unauthorized parties during or after
their period of employment.

---

2. DURATION

The obligations set forth in this Agreement
shall remain in effect for 5 years

following the termination of employment,
regardless of the reason for termination.

---

3. NON-COMPETE

The Employee agrees that upon separation
from the Division,

they will not engage in, consult for,
or be employed by any competing
investigative body or private entity

conducting work of a similar nature
for a period of 6 months.

---

4. PENALTIES

Breach of this Agreement may result in:

- civil liability
- criminal prosecution under applicable
  federal law
- forfeiture of any post-employment benefits

---

5. GOVERNING LAW

This Agreement shall be governed by
the laws of the District of Columbia.

